# 📊 HPC Task 2 - MPI Statistics

![MPI](https://img.shields.io/badge/MPI-Parallel_Computing-blue)
![C](https://img.shields.io/badge/C-99-green)
![Docker](https://img.shields.io/badge/Docker-Ready-blue)
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-green)

## 🎯 Overview

A high-performance parallel program for calculating statistics (Minimum, Maximum, Mean, Sum, and Frequency) from extremely large arrays of integers using **MPI (Message Passing Interface)** for distributed memory processing.

### Key Features
- ✅ **Parallel processing** with MPI for load balancing
- ✅ **Dynamic Hash Table** with automatic rehashing (load factor 0.75)
- ✅ **Memory efficient** - stores only unique values
- ✅ **Handles large integers** (up to ±9×10¹⁸ using int64_t)
- ✅ **Processes 1GB+ files** (145+ million numbers)
- ✅ **Docker support** for consistent environment

### Statistics Calculated
| Statistic | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| **Minimum** | Smallest value in the array |
| **Maximum** | Largest value in the array |
| **Sum** | Total sum of all values |
| **Mean** | Arithmetic average |
| **Frequency** | Occurrence count of each unique value |

---

