## 🚀 Installation & Setup

### Prerequisites

#### Option 1: Native Linux/WSL
```bash
# Install MPI and build tools
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install -y mpich gcc make
```

#### Option 2: Docker (Recommended for consistency)
```bash
# Docker Desktop must be installed
# Then build the image
docker build -t mpi-stats2 .
```

---

## 🔨 Building the Project

```bash
# Clean previous builds
make clean

# Compile the program
make

# Verify the executable
ls -la bin/stats
```

---

## 📝 Generating Test Data

### Small dataset (10,000 numbers)
```bash
for i in {1..10000}; do echo $((RANDOM % 1000)); done > data/input.txt
```

### Medium dataset (100 MB / ~14.6 million numbers)
```bash
python3 generate_text.py
```

### Large dataset (1 GB / ~145 million numbers)
```bash
# Edit generate_text.py and change TARGET_SIZE_GB to 1
sed -i 's/TARGET_SIZE_GB = 0.1/TARGET_SIZE_GB = 1/' generate_text.py
python3 generate_text.py
```

---

## 🏃 Running the Program

### Run with 4 MPI processes
```bash
mpirun -np 4 ./bin/stats data/input.txt
```

### Run with different number of processes
```bash
# 2 processes
mpirun -np 2 ./bin/stats data/input.txt

# 8 processes (if available)
mpirun -np 8 ./bin/stats data/input.txt

# Using oversubscribe (for testing with more processes than cores)
mpirun -np 8 --oversubscribe ./bin/stats data/input.txt
```

### Run with Docker
```bash
docker run --rm -v $(pwd):/app mpi-stats2 mpirun -np 4 /app/bin/stats /app/data/input.txt
```

### Run with Docker Compose
```bash
docker-compose up
```

